The psychology of excessive bidding: why spend more money?
To auction buyers are willing to spend more, to overvalue the goods.
Neurologists and researchers from New York University have been able to discover the neuro-economic basis of this apparently irrational and known behavior.
According to their study on Science magazine, men don't want to stay back in a competition like eBay auction, so they're willing to pay even a higher price.
The research sought to trace the nervous pattern of this "game" to the nervous system level through experimental auctions.
A group of volunteers played the lot, the other group of players participated in an auction while using functional magnetic resonance imaging (fMRI) method examined the active areas of the brain of the participants in the experiment.
In both games the participants could win some money, but in the auction game, where the substantial element is to bid more than the other, the body crawled under the cerebral cortex enters intensively into operation when you lose the game.
This brain area, in addition to other functions, plays a role in the "self-gratification" mechanism of the nervous system.
So according to researchers, the rise of the price is explained by scanning the vehement reaction of the striated body.
To support their theory, the economists of the research group carried out a financial investigation.
In this survey, three groups have tendered against a partner under different conditions.
The control group reported the actual value of the product in question and they made their bet.
To another group besides this they promised that in the event of a win they would receive another $15 prize.
The third group would have received $15 before the auction, but the members of the group would have lost the money in case of a loss of the auction.
The difference between the two groups consisted of the fact that for one of them the win was highlighted, while for the other the loss.
By checking the hypothesis of neurologists the members of the group who played "against loss" were willing to make higher bets of the control group or "vincent".
"These results are not deductible from any of the previously existing economic theories.
In fact, so far these explained the phenomena found in auctions with the joy of winning and avoiding the risk.
Only the methods of creating the neurologic image have helped to resolve the contradiction between the two theories, so that we have reached a third explanation," said Andrew Schotter, professor at the Faculty of Economics at the University of New York.
Hepatitis: when to contact your doctor?
Almost half a billion people in the world suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, but among the first causes of death chronic liver diseases are mentioned in Hungary.
In Hungary the number of hepatitis patients is 100 thousand, of which only 7000 are treated: the reason is that many patients do not know how to be infected.
Hepatitis is the collective name of contagious liver diseases caused by several viruses.
There are many similarities between the symptoms, typical are hepatitis and jaundice, but their pathogens and the diseases caused differ from one another.
Hepatitis viruses are spread in two main forms depending on the pathogenic agent: hepatitis A and E via the food channel (e.g., water and food), hepatitis B, C, D and other blood and organic fluid viruses (sperm, vaginal losses, saliva).
For those travelling it is useful to vaccinate against A and B virus, against C there is no vaccine.
Symptoms of hepatitis A appear two to three weeks after the consumption of infected foods, accompanied by general malaise, weakness, abdominal and nausea.
After yellow spots are formed on the skin and on the white of the eyes, the faeces become clear and the dark urine, the healing takes place within two to three weeks.
One million people die every year worldwide for hepatitis B, the most serious variant of the disease, which causes liver tumors and liver cirrhosis.
The main reason is estimated to be that only one in ten people receive pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: if it is not treated it can cause liver cirrhosis and liver tumors.
Most infected people do not know that they have contracted the disease because pathogens subdolately destroy liver cells, in many cases the first symptoms appear after 20-30 years.
Therefore, it is very important to prevent and carry out regular medical analysis.
This disease is much more frequent than the average in three groups: those who had a blood transfusion before 1991, drug addicts and tattoos.
In the world today, the number of people infected with chronic hepatitis C virus amounts to 200 million.
As a routine laboratory examination also reveals the disease worth addressing to the family doctor when you notice any symptoms of unknown origin.
Recognised in time the disease is curable, the virus can be eliminated from the body, thus the infectious power ceases and the formation of tumors can be prevented.
September 30 is the world day of hepatitis, first organized in 2004 worldwide by sick associations.
The aim is to draw attention to viral chronic hepatitis, the causes of its development and the early recognition of the disease.
