Listening to high-volume music for an extended period of time using portable musical devices such as MP3 players can cause permanent hearing injuries.
It is reported by the European Commission that in a communication published in Brussels, it cites the opinion of the Scientific Committee on Emerging and Recently Identifyed Health Risks (Crsseri) of the EU, published today.
"From this scientific opinion - it is read in the note - it appears that 5-10% of those who, for a period of at least 5 years, listen to music with portable musical devices weekly for more than an hour per day having the high volume apparatus risk a permanent loss of hearing ability."
